<br>
(taken from the developer's corner today)<br>
<br>
&quot;We have been receiving a fair amount of mail regarding the status of changes to classes based on the items brought up in the class talk threads that I started a while ago. Right now I have little new information for you, but let me spend a moment talking about this.<br>
<br>
The team has read and reviewed the lists that I put together. We've had several informal discussions about them, and a few formal discussions about specific items on those lists.<br>
<br>
So far you've seen a lot of changes based on your input. They have been going into the game as they get finished and tested. Things that didn't require a lot of in-depth investigation on our part, such as changing the Bread Pants for Bards, increasing the drop rates for many Kunark spells, fixing the Track Corpse spell and many others.<br>
<br>
And even some of the more complicated issues have been looked into. Things like giving Druids and Shaman the ability to act as secondary healers, upgrading Mark of Karn (a very complicated spell to balance), the aggro created by debuff spells (and, yes, the aggro created by healing spells), and others that have required a lot of consideration have been added or changed.<br>
<br>
We've also started on some of the much more complicated issues, such as Wizards and their ability to do damage against certain NPCs with the Bane spells.<br>
<br>
To finish the lists we'll have to make the time to have some long and complicated meetings over issues that can't be changed without rather a lot of effect on the game world. We have not had those meeting yet. Recently we decided that we would put PvP issues to the forefront, considering that lack of attention they have had over the life of EverQuest.<br>
<br>
I just wanted to let you know that we haven't forgotten the issues that you brought to our attention.&quot;<br>
<br>
So basically, they are not going to get around to it because &quot;we'll have to make the time to have some long and complicated meetings over issues that can't be changed without rather a lot of effect on the game world.&quot;<br>
<br>
Read between the lines - they will not get to fixing our class for another year if at all. <br>
<br>
God this depresses me. What a waste of an investment in this game and company. I can see why they shut down the boards. They really needed to due to the bad publicity they have been getting on not fulfulling what they have promised to do.<br>
<br>
For those of my fellow Wizards that are &quot;happy&quot; with your Wizard, you may have sealed our doom. <br>
<br>
What do I mean by &quot;our&quot;? <br>
<br>
My definition of &quot;our&quot; means the casual, non-UBER guilded gamer. We are the ones that are having to put up with this the most. Not the UBER, multiple sets of equipment, quested armor/robes, etc: type of Wizard. We are the ones having the most problems due to lack of resources, yet our supposedly &quot;pinnacle&quot; brethern as not really helping matters using their UBER sway to tell VI that everything is fine and dandy.<br>
<br>
Looks like the casuals get stuck up the *** again!<br>
<br>
&gt;Anyone have any tucks?&lt; <p>Aziz Al'Qadir
<br>51 Wizard
<br>Order of the Wyrm
<br>Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 5:46:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screwed!</span><hr size=1> &quot;I just wanted to let you know that we haven't forgotten the issues that you brought to our attention.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well considering he posted earlier that they were basically done with balance, that seems unlikely, at best.  Let's just say if they announced all work was done and they were not doing any more work ever... all hell would break loose.  Classes that have been boned by this idiotic decision would lose players even faster than they are now.  So its in their best interest to string ya along. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulndiglow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lndiGlow</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 7:58:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.togrc.com/legends/im_mgif/pl_wizard_mred.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screwed!</span><hr size=1> &quot;Recently we decided that we would put PvP issues to the forefront, considering that lack of attention they have had over the life of EverQuest.&quot;<br>
<br>
There are what....3 pvp servers and how many non pvp servers....why focus on that first?  Why focus on the minority?  <br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
Indi Glow<br>
55 Gnome Wizard<br>
The Doom Guild<br>
