 ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 6:29:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I know, but...</span><hr size=1> At this point, how on EARTH is this a headline?  Is this even SLIGHTLY different than we expected to hear from them?  Are you at ALL surprised????  I mean, honestly.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uazizalqadir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aziz AlQadir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 6:45:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/aziz69?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwi?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screwed!</span><hr size=1> They are basically focusing on the issues that they can take care of easily. Quickest bang for the time invested. Supposedly saving the harder issues up to last. <br>
<br>
In my humble opinion, they are trying to please as many customers as they can quickly, because they know they have seriously ****** up the gameplay for the majority of their audience. Whether they care about this or not - I think we all know the answer to that.<br>
<br>
The only players that are happy are the UBERs, as they still retain their UBERship and can lord it easily over the rest of the player base. Most new quests, items, zones within their new expansion are untouchable by regular players. Hence, the UBERs feel confident and justified in their position of perceived power over VI and the majority of the player base.<br>
<br>
And since VI mainly listens to the UBER player base, that is really only where their attention span has ever been, they feel that if they can cater and develop on this select customer niche, the rest of the player base will be fine. If the UBER base is having problems and complaining about their class/zone/situation, then VI will listen. If they say everything is fine and dandy, VI will put it's attentions elsewhere.<br>
<br>
Well - as listed here in some of the messages within this board - all or most of the folks saying &quot;Oh - Wizards are fine. I have no problems with mine - I wonder why you are whining and so upset? You must not know how to play your character. I suggest you start a different class as I find my Wizard SOOO fulfilling.&quot; This attitude is dangerous for all of the Wizard base, as it sends a signal to VI that Wizards are fine.<br>
<br>
If VI gets this feedback, of course they will not do anything as they have heard from our supposedly &quot;leaders&quot; of the class that at their level everything is ok. What they forget is that not everyone subscribes to play 6+ hours a day and belong to a large guild. Most do not. Currently, if you have a Wizard, you HAVE to be in an UBER guild to get the support you need. <br>
<br>
Those that have posted &quot;their fulfillment&quot; on this message board usually and quite proudly list their guild affiliation. Do me a favor - check out their signatures - look at their guild listings. I am willing to bet that 95% of them belong to large/UBER guilds and have all the support in the world. Now you see why they are so &quot;happy&quot;. I would be too if I could walk around with the lastest gear and boast I had multiple sets of gear &quot;depending on my mood&quot;.<br>
<br>
Well - VI still has not learned their lesson and as a result, had to shut down the regular boards as the player base that is damaged the most by these changes and upgrades are the casuals (the majority of the players).<br>
<br>
The UBERs are wrong. Post 50 game is dead for most folks outside of UBERship. Quests and equipment at this level are way above a casuals ability to obtain. Wizard effectiveness in group situations has been drastically reduced without the proper equipment - hence the vicious circle. <br>
<br>
At this point in the game, players are judged by their equipment in all situations. In looking for groups, folks look at what you have on as a walking billboard as to your abilities/experience. The better equipment you have, the better the chance you have at groupage.  <p>Aziz Al'Qadir
<br>51 Wizard
<br>Order of the Wyrm
<br>Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 8:00:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screwed!</span><hr size=1> Sorry to burst your bubble, but wizards in uberguilds arn't happy either.  The guild I am in now is on the edge of being considered uber(some say we are, some say not quite yet), but in general, the ONLY groups I get into without a lot of grief are guild groups.  And even those who are in uberguilds know that wizards are screwed up in the post 50 game.<br>
<br>
They thought that doing 2k for 21 plat at level 60 to only certain mobs was good?  These people are idiots!  I've tried to post this, but Absor doesn't put it up that the problem is they are too busy working on trivial things like trade skills, rather than working on things to FIX problems.  Who cares about melee stat improvements because you can now bake a cake with magical effects?  Maybe some level 30s, but they don't have as many issues with the game, so don't need that.<br>
<br>
I can see it now, bake items that give a haste bonus for the melees, or perhaps give druids more abilities why don't they?<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 54 Wizard<br>
Call of Ascension<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarundelpajo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arundel Pajo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/12/01 8:21:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screwed!</span><hr size=1> Sadly, I feel that a lot of what you say is right on the money, Aziz, though I am still far from giving up hope on the balance issue.  <br>
<br>
I thank &lt;deity of your choice&gt; every day that I am at the very least in a *large* guild, even though we are very far from &quot;uber&quot;.   I am very lucky to be a part of that.... I was guildless for a long time, and it was a lonely existance.<br>
<br>
